"{\"uid\": \"columbiamissourian.com-sports-pro_sports-former-mizzou-swimmer-dahlgren-places-sixth-in-200-butterfly-finals-at-u-s-olympic-trials-article_521325c8-2e97-11ef-bf79-3ff603fe2166.html\", \"text\": \"    Jack Dahlgren  Former Missouri star Jack Dahlgren finished sixth in the 200-meter butterfly finals with a time of 1 minute, 56.63 seconds at the U.S. Olympic Swimming Trials on Wednesdayat Lucas Oil Stadiumin Indianapolis.  Dahlgren was 1.55 seconds away from qualifying for the Summer Olympics, needing to be one of the top-two finishers in the eight-man finals. Thomas Heilman (1:54.50) and Luca Urlando (1:55.50) finished first and second, respectively, and will represent the U.S. in the event in Paris next month.  Javascript is required for you to be able to read premium content.Please enable it in your browser settings.  Jack Dahlgren  Sports Reporter, Fall 2022 Studying Sports Journalism Reach me at @pcgillam@mail.missouri.edu or in the newsroom at 882-5720  Sports Reporter, Fall 2022 Studying Sports Journalism Reach me at @pcgillam@mail.missouri.edu or in the newsroom at 882-5720      Sports editorblandp@missouri.edu  Associate sports editormsaxon@missouri.edu  Success!An email has been sent towith a link to confirm list signup.  Error!There was an error processing your request.  Get the latest Mizzou and local high school sports stories delivered to your inbox.  Currently in Columbia  Your browser is out of date and potentially vulnerable to security risks.We recommend switching to one of the following browsers:              Account processing issue - the email address may already exist  The Columbia Parents' Digest is a newsletter to keep you in the know about raising kids in Columbia.  Start your day with the latest news stories for Columbia.  Receive a roundup of the news of the day each evening. (View a sample.)  Each week's obituaries, delivered to your inbox.  Join the MNN Newsletter for a behind-the-scenes look at how the Columbia Missourian, KOM